@MattGraves01 No. It wasn't Luke's attachment, it was his selflessness. It turned out to be that way long before he knew Vader/Anakin was his father.

That is why is called RETURN OF THE JEDI, it refers to ANAKIN because he did a selfless act and killed the Emperor, turning into a Force ghost.

The people who wrote Mare Jade really didn't understand the nature of the Force, the Jedi and the dark side or the Sith.

@MattGraves01 Luke used a Force Choke at the beginning of Return of the Jedi and used a black suit. A proof that he was slowly turning into the Dark Side just like his father. 

There is also a flashback in Empire Strikes Back when he kills a Force vision of Darth Vader and he saw himself.

The EU is fun but that isn't canon, specially the "Grey Jedi" and lightside force users using red lightsabers, Force lighting and other similar nonsense...
